text:
Circus--W.P.A.: A traveling circus, operated by the Works Projects Administration, makes its round to various neighborhoods of the city, providing free entertainment to the working populace of New York. These views were taken at Roosevelt Avenue and 92nd Street, Queens.

P. L. Sperr

June 16, 1937
Views 1,2
title: Circus - [Queens].
